## 🗒️ Architecture Notes
- `employment_status` lives on `network_member_roles` (the relationship), NOT `profiles`. Terminating an employee at your business never touches their Supabase auth account — they can still use the app and join other businesses.
- `location_ids` array on `network_member_roles`: `null`/empty = access to all locations.
- `isPremiumProfile()` in `lib/supabase.ts` is the single source of truth for tier checks — handles `role`, `subscription_status`, and trial expiry.
- All dashboard fetch functions read `locationRef.current` (a `useRef`) rather than the `selectedLocationId` state variable. This prevents stale closure bugs where child component callbacks would see the initial `'all'` value.
- `team_members` table may still exist from an old directory API iteration. New system uses `network_member_roles` exclusively. The SQL migration has an optional DROP statement.